voicesplitting.voice

Interface VoiceSplitter

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HmmVoiceSplitter

    public interface VoiceSplitter
    A VoiceSplitter will split a List of MidiNotes into voices. That is, it will take as input a single ordered List of MidiNotes, and return a List of SingleNoteVoices, each List consisting of MidiNotes which occur contiguously in the song in a single voice. For piano, this could be congruent to splitting the notes into right and left hand parts, or it may be separating multiple instruments out into their respective parts.
    Author:
    Andrew McLeod - 1 April, 2015
